#: ../../manual/editors/info/screenshot.rst:21
msgid ""
":kbd:`Ctrl-F3` will take a screenshot of Blender and then open the :doc:"
"`File Browser </editors/file_browser/index>`, allowing you to specify the "
"name and location of the screenshot. In the example image at the right, the "
"``PNG`` format will be the output of the screenshot taken (settings are the "
"same as the ones available to save render results). When the :doc:`File "
"Browser </editors/file_browser/index>` opens, on the left, there is a tab "
"called *Save Screenshot* where you can find format settings and a checkbox "
"with the option *Full Screen*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/info/screenshot.rst:29
msgid ""
"Check the Option to save the entire Blender window (full width and height of "
"the Blender window you are using when you call the command)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/info/screenshot.rst:31
msgid ""
"Uncheck the box to save only your active area (where your mouse is located "
"when you call the command)."
msgstr ""

